channel.title: 317 Rsps Help Please!
channel.description: Can somebody please help me? I'm using TrisidiaX V3 Source. And I changed the IP in Server.java to my ip, but I've tried Hamachi and I've tried no-ip. I have portforwarded the ports 43594 on TCP And the UDP or whatever the second was. But I can't seem to get my server to work online yet. Every time I check if my port is open on 43594, it says it's not. But I have portforwarded and put exceptions in my firewall. Help please? Btw, I was trying to use rswebclients.com for my client. :mad:

item.title: 317 Rsps Help Please!
item.dc:creator: @The_Web_Guy The Web Guy
item.description:
@The_Web_Guy wrote:

Get your own client, don’t use rswebclients.com.
If you’re positive you’ve port-forwarded, try shutting off firewall (if you’re using a VPS)
Also, you change the IP client-sided, not server-sided. When you get your own client, look in GUI, Server, or Client. Sometimes jFrame.
